-- Wulff Leads as German Presidency Vote Goes to Second Round in Berlin Today
-- Alan Crawford
-- 2010-06-30T12:21:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-30/german-presidency-vote-goes-to-second-round-as-votes-for-wulff-fall-short.html

          
          
             German Chancellor Angela Merkelâ€™s
candidate, Christian Wulff, failed to win enough votes to secure
the German presidency in a first round of voting in Berlin
today.  
 Wulff won 600 votes in the 1,244-member assembly, while the
opposition candidate, Joachim Gauck, got 499 votes. A third
candidate, Luc Jochimsen, won 126 votes.  
 Voting will now go to a second round, also to be held
today. A total of 623 votes is needed to win in the second
round. If voting goes into a third round, the candidate with the
most votes wins.  
          
          


  


        